            "value": "%3Cp%3EHow%20easy%20it%20is%20in%20a%20trial%20to%20live%20life%20looking%20through%20the%20rearview%20mirror!%20Job%20could%20not%20help%20but%20remember%20the%20times%20of%20total%20peace%20and%20prosperity%20when%20nothing%20was%20wrong%20and%20he%20felt%20the%20continual%20presence%20of%20God.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESuch%20rear%20reflection%20is%20destructive%2C%20however%2C%20because%20it%20brings%20a%20deep%20sense%20of%20regret%20and%20remorse%20instead%20of%20hope%20for%20the%20future.%20The%20sons%20of%20Korah%20wrote%2C%20%22My%20heart%20is%20breaking%20as%20I%20remember%20how%20it%20used%20to%20be%3A%20I%20walked%20among%20the%20crowds%20of%20worshipers%2C%20leading%20a%20great%20procession%20to%20the%20house%20of%20God%2C%20singing%20for%20joy%20and%20giving%20thanks-it%20was%20the%20sound%20of%20a%20great%20celebration!%22%20(Psalm%2042%3A4).%20The%20effect%20of%20such%20backward%20gazing%20is%20depression.%20%22Why%20am%20I%20discouraged%3F%20Why%20so%20sad%3F%22%20(v.%205).%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPaul%20learned%20to%20no%20longer%20look%20at%20the%20past%20but%20to%20consider%20the%20future%20as%20one%20long%20triumphal%20procession%20in%20Christ%20(2%20Corinthians%202%3A14).%20You%20cannot%20relive%20the%20past-you%20can%20only%20walk%20with%20Jesus%20into%20the%20future.%20Put%20your%20past%20under%20His%20blood.%20Take%20His%20hand%20today%20and%20let%20that%20relationship%20give%20off%20the%20aroma%20of%20Christ%20to%20a%20watching%2C%20waiting%20world.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
